This paper presents a new evaluation measure for co-clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining. Specifically, it focuses on evaluating co-clusterings, which can be applied to various domains such as information retrieval and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
